channel.title: Prototype
channel.description:
[center][size=18pt]Prototype[/size][/center]
[center] I wrote this near four months ago and this was the project that really helped to give me a better understanding of the 317 protocol and the Java language. Now that I look back on this I realize there a lot of things I should have re-written or updated, but oh well. Since I stopped working on this I have written several frameworks privately and a few Java based games and am learning more every day. I'm releasinh this because I was clearing my documents today and found it, I wrote a few updates out of boredom but now I think i'm done with it. It uses the Netty API for a networking system and is heavily re-factored as well repackaged and cleaned. The base is Emulous. If you want to see the content then download it. I'm releasing this because in my opinion RSPS are changing to much for me to try to keep up anymore and since I haven't programmed anything serious in two months. I don't except many to use this because it's not a poorly written server preloadeding 634 content. Prototype was going to be a server made to mimic older servers, not remakes but actual private servers from 2006. Here's a list of in-game features although must of the time was spent on the inner workings.
[left] [size=12pt] Listed Features:[/size]
[ul][li]Perfectly timed combat, including all weapons and specials.[/li] [li]Object Faces read from the cache for perfect object re-spawning.[/li] [li]Near perfect event driven Mining and Woodcutting.[/li] [li]Re-worked Dialogue System & options.[/li] [li]Bank PINS with 100% Runescape Dialogue.[/li] [li]Basic Thieving with timed delays and stall re-spawning.[/li] [li]Netty API and task driven server processing.[/li] [li]Dragon Claws using the Runescape formula but the emotes used in older servers.[/li] [li]Granite Maul special timed perfectly.[/li] [li]Complete clipping for both players and NPC's supporting editing.[/li] [li]Crafting system using the real interfaces, supports D'Hide & Gems.[/li] [li]Cleaned and formatted down to the last line.[/li] [li]Heavily re-factored classes and fixed naming conventions.[/li] [li]Support for multiple clients.[/li] [li]Over 70 NPC dialogues, all with perfect grammar and usage.[/li] [li]Experience locking and unlocking.[/li] [li]Fight caves basics, with dialogue upon starting and completing.[/li] [li]Complete Runescape running system, perfect down to the last detail.[/li] [li]Membership corresponding with days registered.[/li] [li]Region updating system for all objects.[/li] [li]Integration of Cycle events.[/li] [li]Packaged for easy access with an IDE.[/li] [li]Much more, but I am tired of typing.[/li][/ul]
[/left] [/center]
[IMG]http://i50.tinypic.com/2wpnrsk.png[/img]
[center][IMG]http://i45.tinypic.com/2uy2loy.png[/img]
Download: http://up.ht/TKu4cZ[/center]

item.title: Prototype
item.dc:creator: @iz3_legend iz3 legend
item.description:
@iz3_legend wrote:

[size=15pt]Client Connection Troubles[/size]

For any trouble connecting to clients that aren’t Galkons.

  1. Find

headIcon = -1; : set that to 0.

  1. Find

headIconPk = -1; : set that to 0.

That will allow you to use most 317 - 377 deobs. If you get a messed up character, find playerProps.writeByte(headIconPk); and comment it out. This is all done in the Player class. Although then you will have to modify your head icons to fit your new client. The Id’s are probably similar.
